de.hu.gralog.algorithm.result
Class DisplaySubgraphMode

java.lang.Object
  de.hu.gralog.algorithm.result.DisplaySubgraphMode
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class DisplaySubgraphMode
extends Object
implements Serializable

This class represents a display-mode for subgraphs. Here you can specifify display-modes for the vertices and edges in- and outside of the subgraph. The following code shows how to construct and initialize a DisplaySubgraphMode for use in an AlgorithmResult: 

 DisplaySubgraphMode displayMode = new DisplaySubgraphMode();
 displayMode.setVertexDisplayMode(DisplayMode.HIGH1, DisplayMode.SHOW);
 displayMode.setEdgeDisplayMode(DisplayMode.HIGH1, DisplayMode.HIDE);
